workflows.name: Publish docs in the Wiki
workflows.display_title: Addition of setting for whitelisting of IP address ranges (#5188)

head_commit.message:
Addition of setting for whitelisting of IP address ranges (#5188)

* Addition of setting for whitelisting of IP address ranges

* Add a CLI command to manage excluded IP addresses

* Fix exclusion of IP addresses

Unhandled cases when there is a large fragmented list of included IPs:
- an allowed ip range is entirely included in an excluded ip range
- an allowed ip range is equal to an excluded ip range

Now in case of an overlap {ip range A} - {ip range B containing A}

* Add test case for IP address exclusion

head_commit.message:
Remove instances of 'qsTrId("...close")', 'qsTrId("...back")', and 'qsTrId("...getHelp")  (#6422)

* Use 'MZI18n.GlobalGoBack' instead of 'qsTrId("vpn.main.back")'

* Add 'Close' string to strings.yaml and use in templates

* Add 'Get help' string to strings.yaml and use in templates

* Use MZI18n.GlobalClose in MZPopup.qml

* Remove a few additional instances of 'qsTrId(vpn.main.back)'

* Lint: Change getHelp string ID

* Lint roll
